  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of the POST-PCI trial is to compare the clinical outcomes of a
      post-percutaneous coronary intervention(PCI) aggressive management strategy of routine
      noninvasive functional testing to a usual-care strategy of symptom-oriented functional
      testing in patients with high risk clinical, anatomical, and procedural characteristics who
      received PCI with contemporary drug-eluting stent and bioresorbable vascular scaffold.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
